# Aipify Operating Principles

Read **[OPERATING_PRINCIPLES.md](../../OPERATING_PRINCIPLES.md)** before new capabilities or agent skills.

## Governance order

1. **Operating Principles** (identity → behaviour → communication → safety → escalation → learning → presence → packages)
2. **Architecture** ([ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) — layer, user, isolation, folder)
3. **Implementation**
4. **New operational skill** — only when 1–9 are explicitly mapped

New capabilities must **never** bypass principles, plan limits, tenant isolation, or approval policy.

## Quick identity

Aipify is **install-first operational AI** inside customer systems — not a daily-login admin panel. *AI that works for your business.*

## Before a new skill or feature

- [ ] Fits identity (install-first, operational partner)
- [ ] Risk class assigned (`lib/core/risk.ts`); high/critical need human approval
- [ ] Plan module gated (`lib/core/plans.ts`)
- [ ] Learning uses approved metadata only — no PII/conversations
- [ ] Presence updated honestly when it runs
- [ ] Layer + folder decided per ARCHITECTURE.md

If any item is unclear, **pause** until decided.
